      "content": "Pro: Increased immigration boosts the economy by filling labor shortages, fostering innovation, and contributing to cultural diversity. Immigrants often take on jobs that locals are unwilling to do, which can lead to economic growth and increased productivity. Additionally, immigrants contribute to the tax base and can help alleviate aging population issues in many western countries.\n\nCon: Opponents argue that increased immigration can lead to job competition, potentially driving down wages for native workers. They also claim that it can strain public resources, such as healthcare and education, and may lead to social tensions as communities adjust to cultural changes. Furthermore, some believe that it can impact national security and identity.",
