      "content": "i get that, but it feels like the \"benefits\" like innovation and growth are pretty much a given, whereas the wage stuff is always being framed as just a \"concern\" or \"contentious\" even when local workers are struggling. dont you think the consensus is actually leaning way more towards the benefits being a reality and the downsides being way more theoretical?",
